<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Student Resources</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* Fake Educational Site */
        .fake-site {
            max-width: 1200px;
            width: 100%;
            background: white;
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .fake-site h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .fake-site .content {
            color: #34495e;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .fake-site .section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .fake-site h2 {
            color: #3498db;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .fake-site ul {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        .fake-site li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        /* Password Box */
        .password-container {
            display: none;
            max-width: 400px;
            width: 100%;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            text-align: center;
        }

        .password-container.active {
            display: block;
        }

        .password-container h2 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            font-size: 2em;
        }

        .input-group {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .input-group input {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 15px;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .input-group input:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: #667eea;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
        }

        .submit-btn {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 15px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .submit-btn:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
        }

        .error-message {
            color: #e74c3c;
            margin-top: 15px;
            display: none;
        }

        .instruction {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 20px;
            right: 20px;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
            color: white;
            padding: 15px 25px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            animation: pulse 2s infinite;
        }

        @keyframes pulse {
            0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
            50% { opacity: 0.7; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Fake Educational Site -->
    <div class="fake-site" id="fakeSite">
        <h1>ðŸ“š Study Skills and Academic Success</h1>
        <div class="content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Effective Study Techniques</h2>
                <p>Research shows that active learning strategies significantly improve retention and understanding. Here are some proven methods:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Spaced Repetition:</strong> Review material at increasing intervals to enhance long-term memory</li>
                    <li><strong>Active Recall:</strong> Test yourself regularly instead of passive re-reading</li>
                    <li><strong>The Feynman Technique:</strong> Explain concepts in simple terms to identify knowledge gaps</li>
                    <li><strong>Pomodoro Method:</strong> Study in focused 25-minute intervals with short breaks</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Time Management Strategies</h2>
                <p>Balancing academic work with other responsibilities requires effective planning:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Create a weekly schedule blocking out study time</li>
                    <li>Prioritize tasks using the Eisenhower Matrix (urgent vs. important)</li>
                    <li>Break large projects into smaller, manageable tasks</li>
                    <li>Use digital calendars or planners to track deadlines</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Note-Taking Best Practices</h2>
                <p>Good notes are essential for effective studying:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Cornell Method:</strong> Divide pages into notes, cues, and summary sections</li>
                    <li><strong>Mind Mapping:</strong> Create visual diagrams connecting related concepts</li>
                    <li><strong>Outline Method:</strong> Use hierarchical structure with main points and sub-points</li>
                    <li>Review and revise notes within 24 hours of the lecture</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Test Preparation Tips</h2>
                <p>Preparing for exams requires strategic planning:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Start studying at least one week before the exam</li>
                    <li>Create practice tests and study guides</li>
                    <li>Form study groups to discuss difficult concepts</li>
                    <li>Get adequate sleep the night before the exam</li>
                    <li>Review material multiple times using different methods</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Password Box -->
    <div class="password-container" id="passwordBox">
        <h2>ðŸ”’ Access Code</h2>
        <form id="passwordForm">
            <div class="input-group">
                <input type="password" id="passwordInput" placeholder="Enter password..." required autofocus>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Enter</button>
            <p class="error-message" id="errorMessage">Incorrect password!</p>
        </form>
    </div>

    <div class="instruction" id="instruction">Press CTRL+G (or CMD+G on Mac) to toggle</div>

    <script>
        const fakeSite = document.getElementById('fakeSite');
        const passwordBox = document.getElementById('passwordBox');
        const instruction = document.getElementById('instruction');
        const passwordForm = document.getElementById('passwordForm');
        const passwordInput = document.getElementById('passwordInput');
        const errorMessage = document.getElementById('errorMessage');

        // Toggle between fake site and password box with CTRL+G or CMD+G
        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            if ((e.ctrlKey || e.metaKey) && e.key === 'g') {
                e.preventDefault();
                
                if (fakeSite.style.display === 'none') {
                    // Show fake site, hide password box
                    fakeSite.style.display = 'block';
                    passwordBox.classList.remove('active');
                } else {
                    // Show password box, hide fake site
                    fakeSite.style.display = 'none';
                    passwordBox.classList.add('active');
                    setTimeout(() => passwordInput.focus(), 100);
                }
            }
        });

        // Handle password submission
        passwordForm.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
            e.preventDefault();
            
            const password = passwordInput.value;
            
            try {
                const response = await fetch('/check-password', {
                    method: 'POST',
                    headers: {
                        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
                    },
                    body: JSON.stringify({ password })
                });
                
                const data = await response.json();
                
                if (data.success) {
                    // Correct password - redirect to login
                    window.location.href = '/login';
                } else {
                    // Wrong password - show Matrix screen
                    window.location.href = '/denied';
                }
            } catch (error) {
                console.error('Error:', error);
                errorMessage.style.display = 'block';
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>